rComments: Terrible at explaining things. Speaks only in mathematical expressions and poorly-demonstrated examples, and refers you to a textbook riddled with errors and practice questions you haven't covered in class. Professors like these are the reason such a straightforward course becomes so confusing. Likes math, just shouldn't teach it. Avoid this guy!!!
teacherRatingTags: ['Test heavy', 'Get ready to read', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: Pros: his grading scheme (at least with regards to MAT1341). All prior grades were replaced by the exam if they were lower than your exam grade. A life saver if you flunk a test (or 3) Cons: he talks incredibly slowly. So slow that 2x speed still drags on. This also means you cover less material in class, making textbook reading a necessity.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Accessible outside class', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: Prof. Hua is pretty average. He makes some jokes here and there but lectures are quite boring and monotone. In class, he solves easy problems w/o a clear methodology and the difficulty of practice problems is also well below of exams. The exams were multiple choice which was nonsense for a maths class. So all in all great guy but avoid if possible.

Worst math teacher ever. You know those professors who love math so much they expect everyone to understand concepts without explaining them. That's him. Final is nothing like examples or course content. Extremely difficult.

He seems like a nice guy, but is definitely not a good prof. His explanations are not clear and he skips examples. He reads off his PDF and is dull, which is made more unbearable by having to learn online. He tells, he doesn't teach. The midterms are too long for our allotted time. I have always done well in math courses; now I am close to failing.
He is a sweet prof. But his class is super boring.
A good kind-hearted person who is trying his very best.
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Test heavy', 'Clear grading criteria']

rComments: I disagree with the comments that claim that he is a bad professor. He teaches at a slow and steady pace that is easy to understand. He made himself readily available through office hours twice a week. He only counted 3 of the 5 assignments, easy marks. His midterm and final closely reflect the content that was taught in the course. Good prof!!!

Truly disgusted with the quality of teaching from Mr. Hua. Possibly the worst exams Ive ever written, and he is truly the worst professor you can have for this class. Content is difficult, and I highly recommend you steer clear of Mr. Hua in general.

He is a great professor with teaching carefully specifically. He provides notes and his tests are not difficult (similar to previous tests provided). HOWEVER, he has strong accent. You can take it if you do not mind it.

Not a great lecturer, doesn't explain major concepts well enough. He just reads off of his notes and occasionally adds small notes on the typed ones. You need to study a lot to pass the class and read the textbook and watch online tutorials because you don't learn that much in lectures.

I'm absolute garbage at math but I understood all the concepts he taught us. His lectures follow the notes he gives you which I found to be very clear. He explains a concept then gives you examples to demonstrate what he's just explained that actually went a long way in helping me understand.

Dr. Hua supplies excellent lecture notes and clearly explains the course content. He is accessible outside of class for help and provides many previous midterms to practice from. The exams are very close to the previous midterms, so study and you will get an A+. Best math prof I've ever had! Thank you Dr. Hua

Most hilarious prof I've had. Started sitting in the front of his class because he's just so fun and he explains the topics really well. Do the past midterms because the tests are super similar and if you do a couple you'll have no problem getting an A.
He lecture can be quite fast-paced but he has clear expectations of what will be on the test and exam. Go to all his lecture you will do well.
Go to his office hours! He explains really well one-on-one.

He grades his exams as if they're multiple choice. For a whole page problem, if you make a small mistake at the beginning, everything after that will be marked wrong, even if the method is right. If you try to talk to him, he'll say you shouldn't have made any mistakes. Not helpful at all and terrible at explaining.

Spends lectures teaching from a PDF that's filled with examples that he half explains because he assumes that everyone can finish the problem. When asked to clarify he often says the same thing just in a different sentence format.

This prof is a seemingly happy guy but through my own experience he was unwilling to help students before or after class. He would not answer questions from the last lecture. He has a heavy accent and can only understand the students questions half the time.

The guy knows his stuff and is a nice guy but has no clue when it comes to teaching, he would just skip over a good amount of examples and skip steps for the examples he actually did. Don't bother buying the textbook. Half the class failed both the midterms and the final was hard (the final was similar to the review questions sheet he posted)

Dr. Hua is a nice guy who means well. Although he can be very unclear with topics and explanations. He will make the most simplest concepts sound so hard and inconceivable. If you get him, GO TO DGD'S! THEY ENLIGHTEN. His accent is hard to get past, and he won't explain how he got to an answer unless asked, and even then its iffy. Exams are ok

If you are taking this class as a make up course and you didn't do math for a while, be ready to get a tutor. He doesn't explain small math rules that are very important and doesn't develop the exercises. You have to study very hard on your own to pass.

Worst prof. I ever had. I only attended a few lectures and switched to another prof. His lecture is basically he reading a pdf file to class. Never goes to the board. Very hard to understand his accent.

Hua's accent is difficult to understand and he doesn't explain examples very clearly. Some people find this class very easy but I found it difficult because he did not explain very well and would not go over practice questions or examples in class. He is a nice man, but avoid him if you can.

Dr. Hua is a reasonable prof. Lectures for this course were as useful as dookie in a public bathroom. Doing the assignments are as useful as oxygen to live and his course notes are full of typos and missing steps to examples but worth a read. Midterm is easy. Final is bit harder but it was fair. A+ is doable.

Prof is ok, talks really slow, but explains everything very clearly, has typed notes but does written examples in class. Ton of resources available to succeed. Midterms easy if you just do the old ones. Final was hard, very specific and detailed about stuff from the beginning of semester. First half semester is easy, second half is harder

You really had to work for the grade. I found his lectures hard to follow and he moves very quickly! If you miss one class you could miss several topics in one lecture, and examples were few and far in between.

His teaching style fits me perfectly, he has a bunch of notes with example questions for which he goes through in class. His pacing is fair, not too slow and not too fast, so it's easy enough to grasp what he's doing in each question and not get bored. He didn't do a final exam review or really tell us what to study though
He's the best Math professor I've ever had. Clear speech and great board-writing. He has resources that can correct the errors in the textbook. He can easily make students understand hard materials.

He can usually teach concepts and make them clear and easy to understand but you will need to do some more practice yourself. He isn't the most exciting professor but he is able to take you through the steps to learn concepts and work out examples. Overall, he did a good job.
His accent can be a bit hard to understand at times. Just study the old exams and you'll do fine. They are pretty much the exact same thing just with new numbers and values.

Took Mathematics for Engineers. Midterm was marked fairly but the final was not. He didn't look at the procedure you wrote to find the answer. If the answer was wrong, he marked the entire thing wrong, even if the procedure taken was correct but with wrong values. I was on the verge of failing but I went to him and begged him to pass me. I passed.

Take his mat1341, and if you try a little bit hard, i grantee you to get an A+. The content is easy, he gives nice notes on blackboard. Had him for mat1339 as well, and bot got A+, and I never went to lectures, i am telling you. Just learn the notes,and do exercises and you are fine. Tests are exactly from past year with some number changed.
He's a great professor with positive attitudes all the time and make sure you go through the old exams before taking every test.

Great prof: well-paced, knows his stuff, confident, funny at times. Knows how to explain material. Accent wasn't an issue. Pay attention in lectures and DGDs, practice, and you will do well. Provides practice tests with material similar to actual tests. Textbook may be helpful for extra practice material, but I felt lectures and DGD were enough.
I found Professor Hua to be very nice. He's also pretty funny. Hopefully get to have him in higher level math courses. BTW, his English is really good. No language barrier.

Once you get past the somewhat thick accent (which could be an issue for people whose first language isn't English), he's great. He knows what he's doing, is very well prepared, and will take the time to answer your questions. When he does, he expects you to understand or to work to understand if you don't.
He is a really organized teacher.  He knows his stuff really well.  If you attend tutorials and class frequently and do the tutorial questions before the test, you will be fine.  He is nice.

Great teacher. If you study his old exams / notes / tutorials, you should be in pretty good shape as his tests / exams are quite simplistic if you know the basic procedures (MATH 3705 is all 'recipes'). Always has a smile on his face, which makes it all the better!

Prof is great, he makes everything easy, dont expect an interesting though. but he's funny if you notice his jokes lolz. if you have previous exams. study them and you will be good for the course. or just study the notes and the assignments.
Best prof! Hard to understand but you will get used to it! Study old exams because they are exactly the same!

Great math teacher! Heavy accent but speaks slowly and clearly so very easy to follow. Provides notes but writes everything out with good examples. Easy exams and followed class topics/examples closely. Study from previous exams! Funny guy, always in a great mood. He's a monotonous speaker so it's easy to get bored. Make sure you attend class tho!

This class is really boring and the prof doesn't make it any easier. The good thing is if you attend all the classes and do all the practice exams you can pull off an A- or more. The prof is good at teaching the basics but he can't convey the more advanced material to students effectively.
The best pro ! patient and explain question pretty clearly.

Pretty heavy accent but his notes are excellent. He explains slowly and provides good examples. Good about answering questions after class. Midterms and Exam were very fair, quite easy. Just practice with the homework and you're good to go.
Beautiful handwritting, good attitude.
he's hilarious. he always has the biggest smile on his face.

He's a pretty good prof. He's always smiling and making jokes. His english is a little hard to understand at first but then you get used to it and it makes the class interesting. If you can take his class! :)

He's the best math prof I've ever had. I wish I had him for all my math courses! His midterms and final are super easy if you UNDERSTAND the assignments. He's very helpful and very clear when answering questions during his office hours. Always smiling which makes me feel comfortable and whatnot. Should be a full-time professor!
Really uninteresting prof. Hard to understand him with the extreme language barrier. Tests and assignments were easy.
his summer course is pretty easy. his lectures aren't helpful at all. his exams are unbelievably easy!!!!!!
very nice professor

He is pretty respectful of in class questions, does not mind clarifying things. Midterms were pretty easy, and extra marks are usually given without hesitation. Assignments are not tough and they'll prepare you for his tests. Just know the general rules for problems because his questions are designed to see that you know the concept.

Great Proff! I would swear that he's on laughing gas 24/7 haha. All in all very nice and his ability to convey subject matter is very high (if you like math that is). 5/5
Very helpful and friendly. Tests are easy. Although sometimes he talks weirdly, he is one of the best Maths prof I have had.
Nice guy, but class notes not clear. I found the textbook more helpful than the lectures. He's pretty funny though!!!
True, bad english, doesnt use the text, easy midterms, hard finals, his TAs go really easy (at least for me).. really poor attempts at jokes, but if you get what he says you'll ace it. overall. ok
Good prof, needs clearer notes and a more organized Virtual Campus page. Very helpful, funny.

very enthusiastic teacher, very clear when u get to understand him, is always smiling. give him a chance he's cool...so take his class and learn about lective numbers. haha peace................PS he is one sexy boy

If you can get pass his accent (which isn't hard at all) and actually listen to what he is saying, he is a great prof. Why does he repeat the same things over again? Probabably because those things are IMPORTANT. He is very good at explaining concepts, and emphasizes those that are important.

His name is Xing, not Eric.  But anyway, THE WORST PROF IMAGINABLE.  Does not speak english, can not explain math AND DOESN'T EVEN TRY.  Completely useless, in fact his lectures serve more to confuse me than to help.  I'd have literally done better with no prof at all; the material isn't that difficult but he makes it that way. the lec.'s are very clear. i like his teaching way that leave some time during the class let students thinking, and that can follow his step. so that i do not need spend too much time out of the class.
